---

**1. Usage Pattern Analysis**
The WAN link at Hubli_Branch exhibits very low average utilization (1.6% of capacity). Business hours account for the majority of traffic. While an extreme peak of 567.68 Mbps was recorded, this is an anomaly; typical high usage (99th percentile) is only 4.73 Mbps, indicating the link is mostly underutilized. Usage is consistently increasing at 20.85% monthly.

**2. Capacity Planning Recommendations**
Currently, the 20 Mbps link is significantly over-provisioned for its typical usage patterns. Sustained daily peak usage averages 3.15 Mbps. Despite the high growth rate, it will take an extremely long time for current usage to approach the provisioned capacity.

**3. Performance Risks & Bottlenecks**
Congestion risks are minimal, with the link operating in excellent or good condition 99.74% of the time. While extreme bursts are noted, typical peak usage remains well within the 20 Mbps capacity, indicating no current performance bottlenecks from sustained traffic.

**Conclusion**
The link is currently over-provisioned, but its usage trend warrants continued monitoring.
